  "prompt": "What is our body made up of cells or atoms?",
  "response": "Our body is primarily made up of cells, but cells themselves are composed of atoms. Here's a breakdown:\n\n1. Cells:\n- Cells are the basic structural and functional units of living organisms\n- Humans have approximately 30-40 trillion cells\n- Different types of cells form tissues, organs, and systems\n- Cells contain organelles like nucleus, mitochondria, etc.\n\n2. Atoms:\n- Atoms are the smallest unit of matter\n- Cells are made up of molecules, which are composed of atoms\n- Atoms form the chemical building blocks of cells\n- Elements like carbon, hydrogen, oxygen, and nitrogen are key components of cells\n\nSo, while atoms are the fundamental building blocks, our body is primarily organized and functioning at the cellular level. Cells are the smallest living components that can carry out life processes, whereas atoms are non-living chemical units.",
